<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Eurocopter (HCS0011)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><a name="bmStrictlyPrivateLine"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from Eurocopter (HCS0011)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">EXECUTIVE SUMMARY</span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Eurocopter welcomes the opportunity to contribute to the work of the Committee in relation to the safety of offshore helicopter operations.  </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Many factors involving multiple parties are relevant to offshore helicopter safety.  Eurocopter is one of those pa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rties and, as such, recognises the concerns that have arisen as result of the offshore accidents that have occurred during the recent past.  </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Safety is a fundamental part of Eurocopter's approach to the activities of design, manufacture and after-sales sup</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">port of helicopters.  Eurocopter very much hopes that this submission will provide the Committee with a useful insight into those three areas of activity, and looks forward to contributing to any initiatives that may flow from the Committee's work.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">introdu</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">ction</span></h1><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As a leading designer and manufacturer of helicopters for civil and military applications - including offshore oil and gas operations - Eurocopter welcomes the opportunity to contribute to the work of the Committee.  </span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Eurocopter has manufactured over</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> 17,000 helicopters, supplies one-third plus of the global turbine-engined helicopter fleet (to customers in 150 countries), and employs over 20,000 people in its main French and German factories and 30 subsidiaries on 5 continents.  Eurocopter helicopters</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> have accumulated over 85 million flying hours globally.  During 2013, over 3.2 million hours of flying were accumulated by Eurocopter helicopters.</span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Eurocopter products are supported through a network of service distributors, service centres and training fa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cilities with some 140 different partners in more than 35 countries (including a North Sea support and service centre in Aberdeen, and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">19 training centres</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">).  Together with those organisations, Eurocopter is committed to offering local solutions for the ful</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">l range of its products, as well as the highest quality of support services generally (e.g. spare parts, repair and overhaul services, technical assistance, maintenance, and training).</span></h2><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-transform:none">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">At the end of 2012 the total number of helicopters used for oil and gas</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> operations by manufacturer and by region were as follows:</span></h2><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:30.6pt; width:426.3pt"><tr><td colspan="2" style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:426.3pt"><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></h2></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:213.15pt"><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Eurocopter </span></h2></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; bor